South Africa s proposed controversial nuclear deal with Russia is unlawful and unconstitutional and will be set aside, the Western Cape High Court ruled on Wednesday, reports The Citizen.Earthlife Africa (ELA) and the Southern African Faith Communities Environment Institute (SAFCEI) challenged the nuclear deal against the South African government in October 2015 when the organisations discovered that the government was secretly preparing a nuclear power procurement deal.The procurement deal is alleged to have cost the country an estimated R1 trillion and is widely believed to be one of the reasons behind President Jacob Zuma s recent Cabinet reshuffle.The high court set aside all proposed nuclear deals and declared them unlawful and unconstitutional.This is a developing story. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on citizen.co.za